    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense from the realist view, but doesn't that line of thinking just ignore the cost of doing nothing? like, if the US hadn't intervened, wouldn't we have seen a massive humanitarian crisis and potentially even more regional instability from a prolonged civil war or a genocidal regime? isn't it a bit narrow to call it a failure just because the long-term effects were messy, when the immediate necessity might have been the only way to prevent a much larger disaster?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
